15.41	William_Hamilton_(diplomat)	William Hamilton (diplomat)	Sir William Hamilton KB, PC, FRS (12 January 1731 â€“ 6 April 1803) was a Scottish diplomat, antiquarian, archaeologist and vulcanologist. After a short period as a Member of Parliament, he served as British Ambassador to the Kingdom of Naples from 1764 to 1800. He studied Mounts Vesuvius and Etna, becoming a Fellow of the Royal Society and recipient of the Copley Medal.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/ff/William_Hamilton_%281730-1803%29_by_William_Beechey.jpg/220px-William_Hamilton_%281730-1803%29_by_William_Beechey.jpg
